OL,7,FProsecutors argued that the lyrics,
OL,8,Fincluding references to Ms McAreavy
OL,9,Fbeing "hammered and beaten about by
OL,10,Fstrangers" were about mocking the
OL,11,Fmurder of a young Catholic woman in a
OL,12,Fvenue surrounded by Union flags.
OL,14,FThe words used about her in the song
OL,15,Fwere described as "abhorrent".
OL,17,FThe murder victim's widower, John
OL,18,FMcAreavey, provided a statement on the
OL,19,Fdistress caused to him and the wider
OL,20,Ffamily circle by the singing.
