OL,7,FHe set out his belief that there was a
OL,8,Fhateful and hurtful intent behind it.
OL,10,FKelly declined to give evidence at the
OL,11,Fhearing, but during police interviews
OL,12,Fhe denied taking part in the singing.
OL,14,FBut following a contested hearing he
OL,15,Fwas convicted on a charge of behaviour
OL,16,Fintending to stir up hatred.
OL,18,FIn court today a Crown lawyer claimed
OL,19,FKelly has displayed little remorse or
OL,20,Fawareness of the impact on victims.
